The paper deals with optimization of resource allocation in wireless networks, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses distributed algorithms, which falls under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The use of extreme value theory suggests that the paper may also belong to the Mathematical Physics (cs.MP) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses capacity scaling laws, which is a topic in Game Theory (cs.GT).
